==English==

===Etymology===
*Means 50th day in ancient Greek

===Proper noun===
'''Pentecost'''

# A [[Christian]] [[holiday]], which [[commemorate]]s the [[descent]] of the [[Holy Spirit]] upon the [[Apostle]]s, fifty days ([[inclusive]]) after the [[resurrection]] of [[Jesus]] at [[Easter]].
#*'''2005:''' Edward Kessler, Neil Wenborn (editors), ''A Dictionary of Jewish-Christian Relations'' - [[Shavuot]] is linked to [[Passover]] in the same way that '''Pentecost''' is linked to [[Easter]], by a period of seven weeks.
# {{UK}} [[Whitsun]].

